  <section>
    <h1>Index 100 Methodology</h1>
    <h2>A. Evaluation Pillars</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Governance & Integrity</li>
      <li>Leadership & Human Capital</li>
      <li>Innovation & Digital Readiness</li>
      <li>Social & Institutional Impact</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>B. Data Sources</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Public disclosures</li>
      <li>Structured submissions</li>
      <li>Third-party validation</li>
      <li>Advisory review layers</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>C. Governance Firewalls</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Separation between sponsors and evaluation</li>
      <li>Independent advisory oversight</li>
      <li>Conflict-of-interest declarations (mandatory)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>D. Inclusion & Removal Clauses</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Post-inclusion review triggers</li>
      <li>Ethical breach clauses</li>
      <li>Material misrepresentation grounds</li>
      <li>Removal without financial penalty to Index Group</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>E. Appeals Mechanism</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Formal appeal window</li>
      <li>Independent review panel</li>
      <li>Non-public deliberation</li>
      <li>Final determination archived</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>F. Transparency Statement</h2>
    <p>What is public: Index inclusions and high-level methodologies.</p>
    <p>What remains confidential: Detailed submissions and review deliberations.</p>
    <p>Discretion is integral to maintaining integrity in the process.</p>
